<span id="freeTextContainer7101602578332265858">As someone holds New Orleans close to my heart, I could not believe that Fink would go on the Daily Show and laugh at the deaths of people in those horrific conditions at Memorial. I get that its a comedy show, but one must question the wisdom of Fink&apos;s decision to go on Comedy Central to promote the book - unless her ONLY goal is to make as much money as possible off of the tragic events surrounding Katrina. Her flip little behavior enraged me, as I am sure it did others who still suffer the ef</span>
  <span id="freeText7101602578332265858" style="display:none">As someone holds New Orleans close to my heart, I could not believe that Fink would go on the Daily Show and laugh at the deaths of people in those horrific conditions at Memorial. I get that its a comedy show, but one must question the wisdom of Fink's decision to go on Comedy Central to promote the book - unless her ONLY goal is to make as much money as possible off of the tragic events surrounding Katrina. Her flip little behavior enraged me, as I am sure it did others who still suffer the effects of that cruel storm. <br /><br />People on this site have praised her for her meticulous research, but this is selective reporting at its finest. Anyone close to the city or familiar with the complexities of the case knows that Fink followed only the story lines that would make her book as sensational as possible - the truth be damned. The manner in which she treated some of the victims and their families is deplorable. For someone who is trying to position herself as an "ethicist" - she should be ashamed of herself.<br /><br /></span>
